author: alipacala
message:
Refactor Dockerfile to optimize build & production stages with major updates

- The Dockerfile has been refactored to optimize local development, production, and build stages by making use of the docker multi-stage building process.
- The build stage now includes scripts to compile the application from Typescript to Javascript and appropriately sets up the environment.
- The production stage has been introduced to improve image efficiency and provide an isolated environment for the final Docker image.

author: alipacala
message:
refactor: Switch base image to node:18-alpine for development

- Changes base image from node:18 to node:18-alpine for improved security in the development stage.
- Adds --chown=node:node to copy command to ensure the permissions for the files are set for the node user.
- Replaces npm install with npm ci for faster and secure installation of dependencies.
- Removes unnecessary production build steps from the Dockerfile.
